dwhittle branch is contributed by Dustin Whittle <dustin.whittle@symfony-project.com>.

** This branch should be considered unstable and is completely unsupported **
** Most tweaks from this branch are available in the official symfony code **

Dependencies
------------

  Minimum version PHP 5.2.6 with APC + mbstring extensions

  php.ini - enable apc in cli
  ---------------------------
  [apc]
  extension=apc.so
  apc.enabled=1
  apc.enable_cli=1
  apc.cache_by_default=1
  apc.localcache=1
  apc.write_lock=1
  ---------------------------



Differences from 1.1
--------------------

  ORM/Database:
    * additonal configuration options for sfPDODatabase
    * support for PDO based Propel 1.3
      * Propel now uses PDO (instead of Creole) for database API
      * Support for DateTime object and correct handling of pre-/post- epoch dates
      * New nested-set implementation
      * Propel now stores & maps object instances to ensure that only one object instance represents a given database row.
      * New 1:1 relationship support
      * Table and class prefix options
      * Ability to specify custom method names for FKEY relationships
      * Ability to use expressions as default values (e.g. CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
      * Customizable PHP and SQL type mapping on a per-column basis
      * Master / slave support

  Helpers:
    * support for conditionals in js/css
      - condition: IE in view.yml css/js

    * support for xhtml or html style tags
      - use_xhtml_tags in settings.yml

  Tasks:
    * integration of sfOptimizerPlugin + refactored task
    * prefetch task for pregenerating production cache

  Skeleton Configuration:
    * tweaked default settings
    * cache factories now use apc by default

  Environments:
    * added cli environment for symfony command line + tasks

  Routing:
    * based on Francois(routing)/Fabien(trunk)/1.0(bc methods)
    * ajax only routes
    * method based routing

  Response:
    * title is independent of meta


Contributed plugins:

(dw)

  dwCryptPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/dwCryptPlugin

    * Simple interface to mcrypt encryption/decryption

  dwSwfChartPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/dwSwfChartPlugin

    * Helpers for generating swf charts

  dwJpgraphPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/dwJpgraphPlugin

    * Helpers for integrating JpGraph

  dwPrototypeTooltipPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/dwPrototypeTooltipPlugin

    * Helpers for prototype tooltips

  dwPrototypeWindowPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/dwPrototypeWindowPlugin

    * Helpers for prototype window plugins


(Yahoo!)

  ysfDimensionsPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/ysfDimensionsPlugin

    * Dimensions can customize configuation, controller selection, and view selection - very useful for i18n and

  ysfR3Plugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/ysfR3Plugin

    * Integrates Y! R3 I18n library

  ysfBuildPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/ysfBuildPlugin

    * Aggregation/Minification of js/css (YUICompressor) + rewrite view.yml
    * Akamai/S3 url rewriting for static assets
    * Lint Test Tasks: PHP, JS, YAML
    * Cache pregeneration / optimization Tasks
    * Packaging of project as .tar.bz2 and .deb
    * Support for deployment via rsync, libssh2 scp transfer, or ftp transfer

  ysfYUIPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/ysfYUIPlugin

    * css/js framework
    * event system
    * helpers
    * panels/dialogs/modals
    * widgets (datatable)
    * integrated debugger/logging
    * rich admin (ajax filter updates, sortable, inline edit, etc..)

  ysfAPIClientPlugin - http://trac.symfony-project.com/wiki/ysfAPIClientPlugin

    * Adds api adapter for parallel web service requests with curl_multi
    * Adds structure to create web service based object model
